<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <title>How To Use - TaskFlow</title>

        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/reset.css">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/layout.css">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/help.css">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/dashboard.css">
</head>
<body>

    <div class="app">

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <aside class="sidebar">
            <h2 class="logo">TaskFlow</h2>

            <nav>
                <a href="/home">Home</a>
                <a>Chat</a>
                <a>Calendar</a>
                <a>Notifications</a>
                <a>Settings</a>
                <div class="nav-item howto">
                    <a href="/howTo">How To</a>
                    <div class="howto-dropdown">
                        <a href="/howTo#creating-account">Sign in and Login</a>
                        <a href="/howTo#managing">Managing Tasks</a>
                        <a href="/howTo#editing">Editing Tasks</a>
                        <a href="/howTo#search">Search & Filter</a>
                        <a href="/howTo#team">Team Collaboration</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </nav>
        </aside>

<!-- Main Content -->

        <main class="main">
            <h1>How to Use TaskFlow</h1>
            <p class="intro">Learn how to manage your tasks efficiently.</p>

            <!-- Section 1 -->
            <div class="help-section" id="creating-account">
                <h2>1. Creating of Account</h2>

                <p>
                Go to <strong><a href="/signup">Sign In</a></strong> page or click at <strong>Home</strong> at your left. <br>
                At the page you need to fill all fields, <strong>Username</strong>, <strong>Email Address</strong>, <strong>Password</strong> and <strong>Confirm Password</strong>. <br>
                And press on <strong>Create Account</strong> button.
                </p>
                <br>
                <p>Example:</p>
                <img src="/img/SignIn_and_Login/createAccountExample.png" width="400px" height="436px" alt="Example of creating of account">
                
                <h2>2. Login</h2>

                <p>
                Go to <strong><a href="/signup">Login</a></strong> page or click at <strong>Home</strong> at your left. <br>
                At the page you need to fill all fields, <strong>Email Address</strong>, <strong>Password</strong>. <br>
                And press on <strong>Login</strong> button.
                </p>
                <br>
                <p>Example:</p>
                <img src="/img/SignIn_and_Login/loginExample.png" width="400px"  alt="Example of creating of account">
            </div>

            <!-- Section 2 -->
            <div class="help-section" id="managing">
                <h2>2. Managing Tasks</h2>
                <p>
                Tasks are automatically organized into:
                </p>

                <ul>
                <li><strong>Today</strong> – tasks due today</li>
                <li><strong>Week</strong> – tasks due within 7 days</li>
                <li><strong>Month</strong> – tasks due within 30 days</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Section 3 -->
            <div class="help-section" id="editing">
                <h2>3. Editing & Deleting</h2>

                <p>
                Click <strong>Edit</strong> on any task to update it.
                Use <strong>Delete</strong> to remove a task permanently.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Section 4 -->
            <div class="help-section" id="search">
                <h2>4. Search & Filter</h2>

                <p>
                Use the search bar to quickly find tasks.
                You can also sort tasks by date, priority, or progress.
                </p>
            </div>

        <!-- Section 5 -->
            <div class="help-section" id="team">
                <h2>5. Team Collaboration</h2>

                <p>
                Assign users to tasks to work together.
                You’ll see team avatars on shared tasks.
                </p>
            </div>
        </main>
    </div>

</body>
</html>